Class Cognit

java.lang.Object
  com.robix.nexway.Cognit
public class Cognit
extends java.lang.Object

This class contains information about an observed/recognized blob in a Cam image.

Method Detail

getSegImageData

public byte[] getSegImageData(byte[] imgBuf)
Obtains the black and white data for the image which contains the object.

Each byte in the array represents one pixel. 0x00 for black, 0xff for white.

This method copies data into the specified byte array and returns it. If the specified array is null or is too small to hold the image data, a new array is created, filled, and returned.

Parameters:
imgBuf - byte array in which to copy the image data; may be null
Returns:
the cognit's black and white image data

getFitList

public Cognit.Fit[] getFitList()
Returns a sorted array of CognitFits for this object. Cognit 'fits' represent matches to known objects. The first element in the returned array is the represents the closest fit (least error).

This method never returns null. If no fits are available, an empty array is returned.

Returns:
CognitFit[] a sorted array of CognitFits

toString

public java.lang.String toString()
Returns a string representation of the values of this Cognit. This method is intended to be used only for debugging purposes, and the content and format of the returned string may vary between implementations. The returned string may be empty but may not be null.
